# Cross-Venture Shared Design Rules
LONG-TERM. Rules that apply to ALL ventures and the YVON dashboard itself.
Venture-specific overrides → docs/ventures/[name]/DESIGN.md (those files win).
Schema: each rule must have [added: YYYY-MM-DD]. Rules without dates are invalid.
🔴 CRITICAL · 🟡 IMPORTANT · 🟢 GUIDANCE

---

## How This File Fits

[CODE::4LOC]
Override priority: venture DESIGN.md > this file > agent MEMORY.md

---

## 🔴 CRITICAL

[added: 2026-03-01] No hardcoded hex values anywhere in component files — all color values must trace back to a CSS variable token in globals.css.
[added: 2026-03-01] globals.css ↔ tailwind.config.ts must stay in sync. If you add a token to one, add it to both immediately.
[added: 2026-04-19] Minimum readable text: 12px / font-weight 800. Never below either threshold.
[added: 2026-04-19] Never apply a dark overlay on top of a light background image. It destroys the palette.
[added: 2026-05-14] Never use text-white inside .glass-nav or any light-frosted container — use dark navy #0c2c52.

---

## 🟡 IMPORTANT

[added: 2026-03-01] mark components 'use client' only when using hooks, browser APIs, or event handlers — RSC by default.
[added: 2026-04-19] Every scrollable list that can grow needs: maxHeight: 360–420px + overflowY: auto + scrollbarWidth: thin. No unbounded height.
[added: 2026-04-19] Each list item gets its own glass card — no shared container wrapping rows in a list.
[added: 2026-04-19] No drop shadows between stacked cards (no 0 18px 50px box-shadow between sibling cards).
[added: 2026-05-14] Typography scale is defined per-venture in their DESIGN.md. The floor (12px/800) is universal; the ceiling and scale steps are venture-specific.

---

## 🟢 GUIDANCE

[added: 2026-03-01] Prefer CSS variable tokens for spacing and radius values too — not just colors. Keeps theming possible.
[added: 2026-04-19] Dark pill elements (tickers, tab strips, chips on light background): background: rgba(8,16,36,0.58).
[added: 2026-04-19] KPI metric cards: individual cards per metric (not a combined strip). Each card with its own sparkline if applicable.
[added: 2026-05-14] If a design token doesn't exist in globals.css yet, add it there first — then use it. Never inline a new color.

---

## Shared Font Stack

[CODE:css:1LOC]
SF Pro Display is loaded via @font-face in globals.css from /public/fonts/SFPRODISPLAY*.OTF. This font stack applies to all ventures hosted on YVON.

---

## NavBar — Shared Behaviour

The .glass-nav CSS class (frosted white pill) is shared across all screens and ventures.
Text inside: always dark navy #0c2c52
Never text-white inside the nav
Source: app/components/Nav/NavBar.tsx

---

## Glass System Source of Truth

The canonical glass implementation lives in app/screens/ceo-command-dashboard/_overview.tsx.
The documented glass spec lives in docs/ventures/yvon-dashboard/DESIGN.md.

If a venture needs a different visual system, its own DESIGN.md overrides — but the globals.css token convention and the 12px/800 floor still apply universally.

---

## Never Again (cross-venture)

[added: 2026-04-19] Applied dark overlay on a light background image across a screen → destroyed glass palette. Rule: no rgba overlay on any background image.
[added: 2026-03-01] Drift between globals.css and tailwind.config.ts — tokens existed in one but not the other, causing class mismatches in build. Rule: always update both files together.